<body class="sol">
<h1>Measures to Reduce Ecological Footprint</h1>
<div class="row row1">
    <div class="col-md-4 para">
        <div class="card solution-card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Reduce Meat Consumption</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Reducing your intake of meat, especially red meat, can significantly decrease your ecological footprint. Consider incorporating more plant-based meals into your diet, such as vegetables, legumes, and grains. Participating in initiatives like "Meatless Mondays" can also make a big impact over time.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4 para1">
        <div class="card solution-card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Use Public Transport</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Opting for public transportation, biking, or walking instead of driving a car can greatly reduce your carbon emissions. Public transport uses less energy per passenger compared to individual cars. Carpooling is another excellent option, which can help reduce traffic congestion and pollution.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use trains, buses, or subways</li>
                    <li>Join a carpooling group</li>
                    <li>Consider biking or walking for short distances</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4 para2">
        <div class="card solution-card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Reduce Energy Consumption</h5>
                <p class="card-text">You can save energy by adopting simple habits like turning off lights when not in use and unplugging devices when they are not needed. Investing in energy-efficient appliances and utilizing smart home systems to manage energy use can make a significant difference. Additionally, improving your home's insulation and weatherproofing can reduce the need for heating and cooling.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Turn off lights and electronics when not in use</li>
                    <li>Use energy-efficient LED bulbs</li>
                    <li>Insulate your home properly</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>